            "answer_text": "I made this map using data from the 2016 Democracy Index, an index made by the Economist Intelligence Unit:  A higher score means better democracy, based on this, Cape Verde is the most democratic nation in Africa. Countries that follow up with high democratic ratings include Botswana, South Africa, Namibia, Ghana, Senegal, Tunisia, and Lesotho. The least democratic nations in Africa \u2014 flagrantly authoritarian regimes, include Chad, Guinea-Bissau, the DRC, the CAR, and Equatorial Guinea. I left countries like Somalia and S. Sudan blank because of the scarcity of data and lack of government function. Western Sahara is also left blank because it lacks autonomy and a recognized government. ",
