            "answer_text": "Democracy in Africa is fragile and uncertain. Some countries might for one second seem like democracies, then the next you hear about a change in a constitution allowing for prolonged presidency (e.g. Rwanda). The democracy observed in a lot of countries in Europe/Americas is still not the reality in Africa. However, there are some fully democratic nations. Here is a map:  Source: Economist. com There is also a great article by the economist about the nature of democracy in Africa. It\u2019s a good read. Africa\u2019s fragile democracies ",
