            "answer_text": "A democratic country in Africa is Ghana. At least in this West African nation, power has been changing hands for the past 25 years and the will of the people have always prevailed. It\u2019s in fact a multiparty democracy. There\u2019s press freedom, right to an opinion (freedom of speech), freedom of association, human rights are well upheld, etc. Ghana through its democracy is leading a new civilisation in Africa \u2014 a civilisation where institutions rule not man or woman (an individual). ",
