                "href": "/profile/Bert-Sonnenschein"
            },
            "answer_text": "First of all, what is meant by democratic? Is it voting every now and then? Is it how Parliament strives to the largest possible majority? Is it how state institutions function. or is it about how the majority of the people feel the political system should be ran? My country, Mozambique might not be democratic by my other country, the Netherlands, while the opposite might also be true. Many people here believe that better leaders come forward thru a party selection, than a people\u2019's election. So they vote democratically for a less democratic system. ;-) In the Netherlands many people consult an on-line platform, to check what party program is better inline with their political views, but then vote on the party they feel more attached to. Ignorance is a freedom right. ;-) ",
